WEBVTT

00:08.573 --> 00:12.229
That sinkhole
brought us to L.A.

00:12.273 --> 00:13.187
Hey.
[men grunting]

00:13.230 --> 00:15.145
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:15.189 --> 00:16.494
<i>I know who took them.</i>

00:16.538 --> 00:18.366
I remember stories about
a violent group of people

00:18.409 --> 00:20.150
<i>that are called the Exiles.</i>

00:20.194 --> 00:21.586
We're gonna get them back.

00:21.630 --> 00:23.023
I promise.

00:23.066 --> 00:26.026
Mary Beth? Mom?

00:26.069 --> 00:27.462
[crying]
No, no.

00:27.505 --> 00:29.377
Paara and her people
have brought us food.

00:29.420 --> 00:31.379
My people are anxious for
us to return with Silas.

00:31.422 --> 00:32.945
We still need Silas.

00:32.989 --> 00:34.425
We just need
a little more time.

00:34.469 --> 00:35.296
Trust me.

00:35.339 --> 00:36.514
You know that I do.

00:36.558 --> 00:37.646
That's amazing.

00:37.689 --> 00:40.823
This is our way
into the building.

00:40.866 --> 00:42.259
Scott.

00:42.303 --> 00:44.174
You are never going to
believe what happened.

00:44.218 --> 00:45.958
We have to find a way out.

00:46.002 --> 00:48.048
If we take out the guards,
sneak out through the gate,

00:48.091 --> 00:49.179
will you help us, Virgil?

00:49.223 --> 00:50.224
I'll see what I can do.

00:50.267 --> 00:51.268
<i>I let you go.</i>

00:51.312 --> 00:54.097
<i>That was a mistake.</i>

00:54.141 --> 00:56.056
<i>Silas is bringing
me to the Exile.</i>

00:56.099 --> 00:57.448
You drugged me.

00:57.492 --> 00:58.884
This will get you
out of the caves.

00:58.928 --> 01:00.886
<i>It's a map.</i>

01:00.930 --> 01:03.150
<i>Go, get your family back.</i>

01:10.157 --> 01:13.116
<i>[light music]</i>

01:13.160 --> 01:20.036
<i>♪</i>

01:20.080 --> 01:21.777
Hi.

01:24.084 --> 01:25.346
It's not exactly
how I pictured

01:25.389 --> 01:27.043
our first night back together.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.089
[laughs] Me neither.

01:31.091 --> 01:35.704
<i>♪</i>

01:35.747 --> 01:36.792
[keys jangling]

01:36.835 --> 01:38.750
Everybody, get up
and get to work!

01:38.794 --> 01:41.013
[door opens]

01:41.057 --> 01:42.406
Let's go.

01:44.800 --> 01:46.758
We have to find
Virgil, see if he's talked

01:46.802 --> 01:48.151
to the other prisoners.

01:48.195 --> 01:49.631
We wanna get out of here,
we need help.

01:49.674 --> 01:52.634
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:52.677 --> 01:58.379
<i>♪</i>

02:00.250 --> 02:03.210
You all have one job
and one job only:

02:03.253 --> 02:04.733
find this rock.

02:04.776 --> 02:07.127
If you disobey us,
there will be consequences.

02:07.170 --> 02:08.563
But we're not unreasonable.

02:08.606 --> 02:11.043
Do as we say, and you'll
have food, shelter,

02:11.087 --> 02:12.828
protection from animals.

02:12.871 --> 02:16.266
One day, you may even
appreciate that we found you.

02:16.310 --> 02:18.312
Get them to tunnel six.
- Move it right now!

02:18.355 --> 02:20.009
Hurry up! Move it!
[whip cracks]

02:20.052 --> 02:21.184
[shouting]
- Come on, move it.

02:21.228 --> 02:23.882
Come on, everybody! Move it!
[shouting]

02:23.926 --> 02:25.362
- Everybody, let's go!
- Come on, move it!

02:27.625 --> 02:29.584
Honestly, I've
never seen anything

02:29.627 --> 02:31.716
more magnificent in my life.

02:31.760 --> 02:34.937
Aldridge and I were face to
face with a herd of mastodons.

02:34.980 --> 02:36.591
All we could do was run.

02:36.634 --> 02:39.289
I made it to a cave where
they couldn't chase after us.

02:39.333 --> 02:40.638
I went in first.

02:40.682 --> 02:42.292
I thought she was
right behind me,

02:42.336 --> 02:44.860
but when I turned around,
she was gone.

02:46.775 --> 02:48.646
Wait, hold on.

02:48.690 --> 02:49.517
She's dead?

02:49.560 --> 02:52.259
No, there wasn't a body.

02:52.302 --> 02:54.478
She just was not there.

02:54.522 --> 02:56.219
I searched everywhere.

02:56.263 --> 02:59.179
But when I couldn't find her,
I came back to the clearing.

02:59.222 --> 03:00.919
Interesting story, Scott.

03:00.963 --> 03:02.443
Damn it.

03:02.486 --> 03:04.184
Aldridge is the only one
who might be able to help

03:04.227 --> 03:05.489
bring Riley and Josh back.

03:05.533 --> 03:06.969
And you have no
idea where she went?

03:07.012 --> 03:10.190
I wish I had better news,
but no, I don't.

03:10.233 --> 03:11.887
Scott, listen.

03:11.930 --> 03:14.542
Did she say anything to you
about a building?

03:14.585 --> 03:16.370
Silas said that's where
she might be headed.

03:17.893 --> 03:20.025
A building?

03:20.069 --> 03:22.027
What, down here?

03:22.071 --> 03:23.246
That's incredible.

03:23.290 --> 03:25.292
But no, she didn't
say that to me.

03:25.335 --> 03:27.468
Come on, dude.
You were with her for days.

03:27.511 --> 03:29.513
She just said nothing
about her plans?

03:29.557 --> 03:31.428
Bro, the woman
is extremely cagey, OK?

03:31.472 --> 03:33.474
I have to agree there.

03:33.517 --> 03:37.304
If you remember anything
else, any small detail,

03:37.347 --> 03:38.957
you tell me right away.

03:45.137 --> 03:46.704
Oh, hey.

03:46.748 --> 03:48.663
We haven't officially met yet.

03:48.706 --> 03:51.100
You might have picked this up
from context, but I'm Scott.

03:51.143 --> 03:52.232
Yeah, I figured that out.

03:52.275 --> 03:53.711
I'm Izzy.
- I know.

03:53.755 --> 03:55.539
Josh and I are basically
bros at this point.

03:55.583 --> 03:56.758
We clicked right away.

03:56.801 --> 03:58.107
He's a good dude.

03:58.150 --> 03:59.761
He said that you were
the brains of the family.

04:01.589 --> 04:03.721
- He did?
- Yeah.

04:03.765 --> 04:05.810
I still can't
believe he's gone.

04:06.463 --> 04:07.725
One minute, he and Riley
were here,

04:07.769 --> 04:10.815
and the next they're in 1988.

04:12.339 --> 04:14.906
You know, I didn't realize
how much I would miss him.

04:14.950 --> 04:16.299
He's gonna be OK.

04:17.735 --> 04:18.910
Is he, though?

04:18.954 --> 04:20.260
Yeah.

04:20.303 --> 04:22.479
I mean, OK, since
he's been down here,

04:22.523 --> 04:25.743
Josh has survived a wolf
attack, a monster of a storm,

04:25.787 --> 04:27.745
and being chased out
of an ancient fort.

04:27.789 --> 04:30.487
So I'm pretty sure he
could make it in 1988.

04:30.531 --> 04:33.098
Worst case scenario,
he comes back with a mullet.

04:33.142 --> 04:35.013
[laughs]

04:35.057 --> 04:36.363
You know,
strangely I can--

04:36.406 --> 04:37.494
I can totally see
him with a mullet.

04:37.538 --> 04:39.409
- [laughs]
- Look.

04:40.845 --> 04:43.848
<i>[eerie music]</i>

04:43.892 --> 04:45.328
Who are they?

04:45.372 --> 04:47.025
Oh, that's Paara
and her villagers.

04:47.069 --> 04:50.159
They're friends,
so nothing to worry about.

04:50.202 --> 04:52.117
Are you sure about that?

04:52.161 --> 04:53.423
They're here for Silas.

04:53.467 --> 04:55.338
Let me talk to Paara.

04:58.254 --> 04:59.429
Paara.

04:59.473 --> 05:00.952
Where is he, Ty?

05:02.040 --> 05:04.042
Can we have
a moment in private?

05:04.086 --> 05:06.915
Anything you say to her,
you can say to us.

05:06.958 --> 05:08.699
It's OK, Joseph.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.533
He isn't here, is he?

05:16.577 --> 05:18.318
No, he's not.

05:18.361 --> 05:20.450
It was out of our control.

05:20.494 --> 05:22.060
Eve and Levi have been taken.

05:22.104 --> 05:24.628
Silas was the only
one who could help.

05:24.672 --> 05:27.370
He's out looking for
them with Eve's husband.

05:29.329 --> 05:31.026
Eve's husband?

05:33.376 --> 05:35.160
You mean Isaiah?

05:35.204 --> 05:37.119
His name's Gavin, but yeah.

05:38.338 --> 05:39.817
He's back.

05:41.689 --> 05:45.780
I'm sorry, but this
doesn't change anything.

05:45.823 --> 05:47.564
We gave you food and supplies.

05:47.608 --> 05:48.913
We helped you.

05:48.957 --> 05:51.176
And you promised us
Silas would be returned

05:51.220 --> 05:52.439
to stand for his actions.

05:52.482 --> 05:55.398
And he will the moment
that they're back.

05:56.312 --> 06:00.751
My people warned me again
and again about taking

06:00.795 --> 06:03.363
the word of the sky people.

06:03.406 --> 06:05.626
What am I supposed
to tell them now?

06:05.669 --> 06:08.759
Tell them that you'll
give me a little more time.

06:11.458 --> 06:13.808
I've already
given you more time.

06:13.851 --> 06:15.200
I thought I could trust you.

06:15.244 --> 06:17.159
Of course you can trust me.

06:17.202 --> 06:18.639
If it looks like
I've been compromised

06:18.682 --> 06:20.380
by the relationship we had--

06:23.078 --> 06:24.645
Had?

06:28.518 --> 06:29.998
Paara, you don't mean that.

06:31.565 --> 06:33.654
You've made your choice.

06:33.697 --> 06:35.395
Now I have to make mine.

06:36.526 --> 06:39.616
Joseph, take the food,
all of it.

06:39.660 --> 06:41.879
Paara, wait.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.098
Please.

06:43.925 --> 06:45.579
Please!
- Hey, hey.

06:45.622 --> 06:46.667
What's going on?

06:46.710 --> 06:47.798
Yeah, no, no, no, wait.

06:47.842 --> 06:49.104
We'll starve without this food.

06:49.147 --> 06:50.235
Stop, OK?

06:50.279 --> 06:51.715
Ah! Hey!
- Take all the food.

06:51.759 --> 06:52.760
Hey, what the hell
you think you're doing?

06:52.803 --> 06:55.066
Back up, back up now!

06:55.110 --> 06:56.459
Back up.

06:56.503 --> 06:58.461
Get back.
- Easy, easy.

07:00.811 --> 07:01.769
Paara.

07:02.683 --> 07:04.467
Get the food.

07:04.511 --> 07:07.470
[frightened chatter]

07:09.167 --> 07:13.911
<i>♪</i>

07:13.955 --> 07:16.479
Paara, it doesn't
have to be this way.

07:16.523 --> 07:23.617
<i>♪</i>

07:28.970 --> 07:31.712
[slaves grunting]

07:32.930 --> 07:34.584
Hey.

07:38.153 --> 07:39.459
Come on.

07:41.069 --> 07:42.287
Virgil.

07:42.331 --> 07:43.506
Any news?

07:43.550 --> 07:44.638
Yeah.

07:44.681 --> 07:46.466
I talked to the
other prisoners.

07:46.509 --> 07:48.816
I got a dozen of them on board.

07:48.859 --> 07:50.992
I told them be ready
this afternoon.

07:51.035 --> 07:54.735
Every time the Exiles change
shifts, they open the gate.

07:54.778 --> 07:56.476
Four leave, four enter.

07:56.519 --> 07:57.868
When that happens,
we rush the gate,

07:57.912 --> 07:59.609
take out anyone
who's in our way.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.351
You two, take that out.

08:02.394 --> 08:04.005
You, go to tunnel three.

08:04.048 --> 08:05.267
Let's go!

08:10.359 --> 08:11.708
Dump that over there.

08:12.883 --> 08:14.711
Dump that right there.

08:17.540 --> 08:19.194
Move it!
Come on!

08:24.504 --> 08:25.853
Eve.

08:27.028 --> 08:28.029
Eve!

08:30.292 --> 08:37.212
<i>♪</i>

08:54.490 --> 08:55.839
Gavin.

08:56.579 --> 09:00.235
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:05.893 --> 09:07.459
I can't believe
you're actually here.

09:08.591 --> 09:10.506
Yeah, I can't
believe it either.

09:11.855 --> 09:15.903
How did--

09:15.946 --> 09:18.209
How did this happen? What--

09:18.253 --> 09:20.081
Izzy, is she OK?

09:20.124 --> 09:22.474
She's fine.

09:22.518 --> 09:23.737
Hey.

09:23.780 --> 09:25.521
Did they hurt you?

09:25.565 --> 09:26.653
Did they hurt you?
- No, no.

09:26.696 --> 09:28.132
I'm fine.

09:29.481 --> 09:31.179
Gavin, I--

09:31.222 --> 09:33.703
I have to
tell you something.

09:33.747 --> 09:35.357
It's about Josh.

09:35.400 --> 09:37.881
No, I know about 1988.

09:37.925 --> 09:40.754
I made it to the clearing.
They told me everything.

09:40.797 --> 09:43.495
We're gonna get Josh back
once we get out of here.

09:44.888 --> 09:50.024
And we're gonna find
a way back home together.

09:50.067 --> 09:51.808
As a family.

09:59.686 --> 10:01.122
Gavin?

10:01.165 --> 10:02.645
Levi.

10:08.825 --> 10:10.697
- Hey.
- Hey.

10:12.394 --> 10:14.091
How the hell
did you get here?

10:14.135 --> 10:17.181
Went through
a sinkhole in Seattle.

10:17.225 --> 10:18.792
Somehow it brought
me to Los Angeles.

10:18.835 --> 10:20.315
So there's a way home.

10:22.622 --> 10:24.232
No. No.

10:24.275 --> 10:26.626
No, that portal closed.

10:26.669 --> 10:31.065
But, hey, I have a way
we can get out of here.

10:31.108 --> 10:36.766
<i>♪</i>

10:37.419 --> 10:39.726
Great.
Back to square one.

10:39.769 --> 10:41.684
And Eve isn't here to
lead a hunt this time.

10:41.728 --> 10:42.946
If I have to go back
to eating mushrooms,

10:42.990 --> 10:44.078
I'm gonna lose it.

10:44.121 --> 10:46.297
Sam, can I have a word?

10:48.517 --> 10:49.692
Look.

10:49.736 --> 10:51.433
Normally, I'm not
one to point fingers.

10:51.476 --> 10:52.739
But you should
have handed Silas over

10:52.782 --> 10:53.783
when you had the chance.

10:53.827 --> 10:54.741
I'm not apologizing
for trying

10:54.784 --> 10:56.133
to get my daughter back.

10:56.177 --> 10:57.874
You've endangered
the lives of everyone here.

10:57.918 --> 11:00.181
Hey, you were a part
of the conversation.

11:00.224 --> 11:01.661
We both agreed to let him go.

11:01.704 --> 11:03.445
We need to survive
down here, Sam.

11:03.488 --> 11:04.751
Paara was our best
shot of doing that.

11:04.794 --> 11:06.622
We don't know the
land like they do.

11:06.666 --> 11:09.712
Now her village will
never trust us again.

11:09.756 --> 11:11.061
Oh.

11:11.105 --> 11:13.498
No, you mean Paara will
never trust you again.

11:14.456 --> 11:17.111
Sam, we are in trouble.

11:17.154 --> 11:18.678
Look at what we have left.

11:18.721 --> 11:21.115
There's maybe a day's
worth of food here.

11:21.158 --> 11:22.464
A day's?

11:22.507 --> 11:23.857
This won't last
till the afternoon.

11:23.900 --> 11:27.469
Guys, we can deal
with this ourselves.

11:27.512 --> 11:29.253
We'll live off the land--

11:29.297 --> 11:30.994
hunt, fish.

11:31.038 --> 11:33.170
Just like humans have done
for thousands of years.

11:33.214 --> 11:34.650
Sam, I'm an accountant.

11:34.694 --> 11:36.478
I mean, that guy over there,
he makes TikToks

11:36.521 --> 11:37.958
about licking random objects.

11:38.001 --> 11:40.482
We're not exactly cut out
to be hunter-gatherers.

11:40.525 --> 11:41.439
You know what
else humans have done

11:41.483 --> 11:42.658
for thousands of years?

11:42.702 --> 11:44.834
Steal.

11:44.878 --> 11:45.879
What are you saying?

11:45.922 --> 11:47.402
I'm saying
we go to the village

11:47.445 --> 11:49.709
and take our food back.

11:49.752 --> 11:52.233
That will only make
a bad situation even worse.

11:52.276 --> 11:54.670
On that, we agree.

11:54.714 --> 11:57.020
Stealing from them is
a declaration of war.

11:57.064 --> 11:58.761
OK. I know I'm new here,

11:58.805 --> 12:01.024
but I'm not so much up for
a war with people

12:01.068 --> 12:02.504
who have actual weapons.

12:02.547 --> 12:04.811
Me neither.
I hate war.

12:04.854 --> 12:08.292
But I kinda hate the idea
of us starving even more.

12:08.336 --> 12:10.164
I'm with Lucas.

12:10.207 --> 12:11.992
You are?

12:12.035 --> 12:13.645
Stealing isn't an option.

12:13.689 --> 12:15.343
Well, how about
we make it an option?

12:15.386 --> 12:16.779
Take it to a vote.

12:16.823 --> 12:19.086
Yeah, who here is against
starving to death?

12:19.129 --> 12:20.652
- Yeah, let's do it.
- I am.

12:20.696 --> 12:22.219
Huh?

12:22.872 --> 12:24.787
OK.

12:24.831 --> 12:27.181
And who thinks
instigating a war

12:27.224 --> 12:29.183
with a heavily armed village

12:29.226 --> 12:32.621
is a terrible idea that should
never be spoken of again?

12:32.664 --> 12:34.188
- Me!
- Absolutely.

12:34.231 --> 12:35.624
- Yep.
- Yeah.

12:35.667 --> 12:37.757
- Absolutely.
- I--yeah.

12:40.803 --> 12:41.935
Then it's final.

12:41.978 --> 12:44.633
There'll be no stealing
from the village.

12:44.676 --> 12:46.722
OK.

12:46.766 --> 12:48.898
Y'all know who to blame
when you go hungry.

12:51.814 --> 12:52.859
[sighs]

12:56.079 --> 12:57.907
Hey.

12:57.951 --> 12:59.648
What's up?

12:59.691 --> 13:03.086
I just wanted to say thank
you again for saving my life.

13:03.130 --> 13:04.914
Don't mention it.

13:04.958 --> 13:08.570
Anyway, um, if you ever
need anything, just ask.

13:08.613 --> 13:10.833
Thanks.
I'm--I'm good.

13:12.922 --> 13:15.403
Lucas.

13:16.578 --> 13:19.537
I'm really sorry
about your mom.

13:21.539 --> 13:24.281
Oh.
Uh, yeah.

13:25.369 --> 13:27.241
Me, too.

13:27.284 --> 13:29.330
Lucas. Oh--

13:30.461 --> 13:31.506
Am I interrupting something?

13:31.549 --> 13:33.421
What do you need, Scott?

13:33.464 --> 13:35.597
OK, so I was just
talking to Judah now,

13:35.640 --> 13:37.860
and we don't care
about the vote.

13:37.904 --> 13:40.167
We wanna go to the village
and take our food back.

13:40.210 --> 13:41.342
What do you say?
You still in?

13:41.385 --> 13:43.083
Hold on.
Sam just said--

13:43.126 --> 13:44.998
Sam's not the boss down here.

13:45.041 --> 13:46.303
OK, maybe he is.

13:46.347 --> 13:48.044
Think of it as
an act of defiance.

13:48.088 --> 13:49.698
So you want to pick
a fight with the people

13:49.741 --> 13:51.613
that tried to kill you before?

13:51.656 --> 13:53.049
You really think
that's a good idea?

13:53.093 --> 13:54.790
Well, I am fairly hungry.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.270
OK, not that I disagree
with you, Scott, but this is--

13:56.313 --> 13:57.575
it's not exactly your MO.

13:57.619 --> 13:59.273
What's your angle?

13:59.316 --> 14:01.057
What? Angle?

14:01.101 --> 14:02.624
I have no angle.
- Come on, dude.

14:02.667 --> 14:04.495
You've been acting
weird ever since you got back

14:04.539 --> 14:06.323
from your little trip
with Aldridge.

14:07.934 --> 14:09.849
Tell me I'm wrong.

14:12.329 --> 14:13.417
Look.

14:13.461 --> 14:14.462
Am I scared?

14:14.505 --> 14:16.812
Absolutely.

14:16.856 --> 14:18.379
I'm not an idiot.

14:18.422 --> 14:21.512
That's why I need you.

14:24.167 --> 14:26.300
- All right.
- What?

14:26.343 --> 14:27.779
It'll be fine.
We know where the fort's

14:27.823 --> 14:29.216
secret entrance is
from last time.

14:29.259 --> 14:30.826
No, it's way too dangerous!

14:30.870 --> 14:33.089
Veronica, we will be in
and out before they know it.

14:33.133 --> 14:36.005
Exactly.

14:36.049 --> 14:38.660
What?

14:38.703 --> 14:41.010
Fine.
Then I'm coming, too.

14:42.446 --> 14:44.013
- Really?
- Yeah.

14:45.362 --> 14:46.886
Like I said, you saved my life.

14:48.278 --> 14:49.540
OK.

14:49.584 --> 14:51.542
And just like that,
we have a crew.

14:51.586 --> 14:55.720
<i>♪</i>

15:00.551 --> 15:02.727
The main entrance
to the cave is here.

15:02.771 --> 15:04.164
This back tunnel
is the only other exit.

15:04.207 --> 15:05.556
We just have to make sure
we get there without being

15:05.600 --> 15:06.862
noticed by the guards.

15:06.906 --> 15:08.733
How did you get your
hands on this map?

15:10.518 --> 15:12.085
Silas gave it to me.

15:13.782 --> 15:15.262
- But then we can't trust--
- Levi.

15:15.305 --> 15:16.785
I know he's your grandfather,

15:16.828 --> 15:18.918
but he was willing to let
Josh and Izzy die.

15:18.961 --> 15:20.920
He's not a good person.
- OK.

15:20.963 --> 15:22.965
I wouldn't have made
it to you without him.

15:23.009 --> 15:25.228
OK? I'm not saying
I forgive what he's done.

15:25.272 --> 15:26.795
But I do believe this is real.

15:28.188 --> 15:29.841
Let's say that it is.

15:29.885 --> 15:32.105
To get to the back tunnels
is not gonna be easy.

15:32.148 --> 15:33.671
The Exiles are everywhere.

15:33.715 --> 15:35.499
They're mining every inch
of this place.

15:35.543 --> 15:37.588
You know, I've seen
that rock before.

15:37.632 --> 15:39.982
The village I grew up in
used it as a fuel source.

15:40.635 --> 15:42.158
They're mining
tons of it here.

15:42.202 --> 15:43.899
I wonder what
they're using it for.

15:43.943 --> 15:46.989
All we know is that they're
transporting it somewhere.

15:47.033 --> 15:49.513
We don't know where.
We don't know why.

15:49.557 --> 15:51.254
Listen.

15:51.298 --> 15:53.213
I--I just can't put our hopes
of getting out of here

15:53.256 --> 15:54.823
on Silas's word.

15:56.694 --> 15:59.654
OK.
So you guys have a better idea?

16:00.698 --> 16:03.049
Yeah, we do.

16:03.092 --> 16:07.009
Every day, when the
guards change shifts,

16:07.053 --> 16:08.271
they open that gate.

16:08.315 --> 16:10.012
The next time they do,
one of the prisoners

16:10.056 --> 16:11.971
is gonna fake
a heart attack.

16:12.014 --> 16:13.885
We're going to take that
chance to overwhelm them

16:13.929 --> 16:15.670
and then make a run for it.

16:15.713 --> 16:17.672
No, that sounds risky.

16:17.715 --> 16:19.195
We've already got
a dozen prisoners on board.

16:19.239 --> 16:20.544
There's more of us
than there are of them.

16:20.588 --> 16:22.590
But if we use the map,
no one gets hurt.

16:24.026 --> 16:26.507
- [sighs]
- What do you think, Eve?

16:28.988 --> 16:32.556
[sighs]

16:32.600 --> 16:35.037
I don't trust Silas.

16:35.081 --> 16:36.038
I'm sorry.

16:36.082 --> 16:38.127
I don't.

16:43.045 --> 16:46.309
OK, fine.

16:46.353 --> 16:47.876
So how can I help?

16:51.053 --> 16:53.142
[guards shouting]

16:53.186 --> 16:55.318
Wait for my signal.

16:55.362 --> 17:02.282
<i>♪</i>

17:10.551 --> 17:11.508
You good?

17:11.552 --> 17:13.467
Yeah.

17:13.510 --> 17:14.685
Listen, I appreciate
you getting

17:14.729 --> 17:16.339
on board with this plan,
I do.

17:16.383 --> 17:17.645
- Of course.
- Thank you.

17:17.688 --> 17:18.994
Yeah.

17:20.474 --> 17:22.780
Gavin, you seem different.

17:22.824 --> 17:24.565
In a good way, right?

17:24.608 --> 17:26.697
Yeah.
Yeah, in a good way.

17:26.741 --> 17:28.873
Like the person I used to know.
It--

17:28.917 --> 17:31.093
It suits you.
- Eve,

17:31.137 --> 17:32.747
it's gonna be OK.

17:35.880 --> 17:37.926
Shift change.
Let's go.

17:39.841 --> 17:42.148
All right, you two.
It's time to take a break.

17:42.191 --> 17:43.888
- Let's do it.
- Come on, let's go.

17:44.628 --> 17:46.152
All done in tunnel 5.

17:47.022 --> 17:49.546
Hey, I need you to go down
in there with 'em, all right?

17:49.590 --> 17:56.727
<i>♪</i>

17:57.772 --> 18:01.732
[coughing, groaning]

18:01.776 --> 18:02.907
Somebody help!

18:02.951 --> 18:04.039
I think he's having
a heart attack!

18:04.083 --> 18:05.910
What's going on in there?

18:05.954 --> 18:07.869
Hey, get up!
Get up, old man!

18:09.088 --> 18:10.176
[grunting]

18:10.785 --> 18:12.047
[grunts]

18:12.091 --> 18:13.614
Let's go!

18:16.051 --> 18:17.966
[grunting]

18:21.622 --> 18:22.927
Let's go!
Come on!

18:22.971 --> 18:25.104
Go, go! Go, go, go!

18:25.147 --> 18:26.279
[screaming]

18:26.322 --> 18:28.455
[grunting]

18:28.498 --> 18:29.499
[screaming]

18:29.543 --> 18:31.240
[grunts]

18:33.808 --> 18:35.462
Levi, they're
closing the gate!

18:35.505 --> 18:36.941
Get everyone outside.
We'll meet you there.

18:36.985 --> 18:38.247
OK. Be careful.
Come on, come on!

18:38.291 --> 18:39.988
Go! Go!

18:40.815 --> 18:42.208
Come on, let's move.

18:42.251 --> 18:43.513
It's blocked.

18:43.557 --> 18:45.298
Go, go, go! Come on!

18:45.341 --> 18:50.346
<i>♪</i>

18:50.390 --> 18:52.740
[grunting]

18:54.524 --> 18:58.311
<i>♪</i>

18:58.354 --> 18:59.442
[both grunting]

18:59.486 --> 19:01.401
[straining]

19:01.444 --> 19:03.011
Levi, I can't hold it!

19:05.274 --> 19:06.319
Grab that shovel.

19:06.362 --> 19:08.799
Go, go!

19:08.843 --> 19:10.671
[gears clanking]

19:12.238 --> 19:13.848
- It's not holding.
- Go.

19:14.327 --> 19:15.763
Levi, go.

19:15.806 --> 19:17.199
I'm not leaving you.

19:17.243 --> 19:18.679
Go with Eve--
- No, Gavin.

19:18.722 --> 19:20.333
Levi, go!

19:20.376 --> 19:22.291
Go. Go!

19:22.335 --> 19:24.511
<i>♪</i>

19:24.554 --> 19:26.208
[grunting]

19:26.252 --> 19:30.647
<i>♪</i>

19:30.691 --> 19:31.735
Where's Gavin?

19:31.779 --> 19:32.867
He's coming.

19:34.303 --> 19:36.827
[straining]

19:39.787 --> 19:46.881
<i>♪</i>

19:52.930 --> 19:54.671
[panting] OK. OK.

19:55.759 --> 19:57.631
Everyone, grab a weapon. Move.

19:59.502 --> 20:01.287
- Come on!
- Go, go, go, go!

20:01.330 --> 20:03.158
- Come on!
- Go, go!

20:03.202 --> 20:04.681
Come on!

20:06.379 --> 20:08.207
[horses neighing]

20:09.860 --> 20:13.212
<i>♪</i>

20:13.255 --> 20:14.735
Damn it.

20:21.132 --> 20:22.873
Drop your weapons.

20:22.917 --> 20:24.223
I said, drop 'em.

20:26.007 --> 20:28.357
Guys, we're outnumbered.

20:28.401 --> 20:30.968
[weapons clattering]

20:31.012 --> 20:33.536
All of you, on your knees!

20:41.065 --> 20:43.198
Do we look like fools to you?

20:44.243 --> 20:48.072
You think we're stupid enough
to just let you escape?

20:48.116 --> 20:49.770
Take them to the cells.

20:49.813 --> 20:51.380
Punish them all!

20:52.468 --> 20:54.383
Wait! Hey.
Wait, wait!

20:54.427 --> 20:55.689
It was all my idea.

20:55.732 --> 20:57.125
Punish me, and let
anyone else go.

20:57.168 --> 20:58.387
- Gavin, no.
- Don't do this.

20:58.431 --> 20:59.649
Don't do this!

21:01.216 --> 21:03.000
Big, strong man.

21:03.044 --> 21:05.133
Think you're brave?

21:05.176 --> 21:06.352
Is that it?

21:06.395 --> 21:07.701
I think, if you
punish everyone,

21:07.744 --> 21:09.398
you'll have no
one left to work.

21:10.965 --> 21:12.836
But you can make an
example out of me.

21:16.100 --> 21:19.060
<i>[intense music]</i>

21:19.103 --> 21:23.630
<i>♪</i>

21:23.673 --> 21:25.414
Put the rest of them to work.

21:26.894 --> 21:28.504
But not him.

21:31.115 --> 21:32.334
Take him.

21:32.378 --> 21:34.336
<i>♪</i>

21:34.380 --> 21:36.295
- [grunts]
- Gavin!

21:37.121 --> 21:38.427
Gavin!

21:39.602 --> 21:42.518
12 paces left,
17 paces right,

21:42.562 --> 21:44.912
13 paces straight.

21:44.955 --> 21:49.133
12 paces left, 17 paces right,
13 paces straight.

21:49.177 --> 21:50.831
What are you saying?

21:50.874 --> 21:52.223
Nothing.

21:52.267 --> 21:53.660
Just a nervous habit.

21:56.053 --> 21:58.882
You know, you don't have
to go through with this.

21:58.926 --> 22:02.321
I'm afraid the train's
already left the station.

22:02.364 --> 22:04.323
Why is this so
important to you?

22:05.628 --> 22:07.543
Come on.
I know there's more going on.

22:09.458 --> 22:11.242
- I have my reasons.
- Which are?

22:11.286 --> 22:12.505
Complicated.

22:13.462 --> 22:14.724
You really are persistent.

22:14.768 --> 22:16.552
You know that?
- Mm-hmm.

22:17.945 --> 22:22.297
Look,
I just care about you guys,

22:22.341 --> 22:24.299
about everyone in the clearing.

22:24.343 --> 22:26.649
I want to protect them.

22:26.693 --> 22:30.653
It's something that I
haven't always excelled at.

22:35.005 --> 22:36.746
[chatter]

22:36.790 --> 22:38.269
Whoa!
Hey, hey, hey.

22:38.313 --> 22:39.445
Get down, get down, get down.

22:49.803 --> 22:52.022
OK.

22:52.066 --> 22:53.633
So that's the front gate.

22:53.676 --> 22:55.156
Secret entrance is
around the side.

22:55.199 --> 22:56.505
Let's go.

22:56.549 --> 23:00.857
<i>♪</i>

23:00.901 --> 23:02.772
Stay low.

23:07.473 --> 23:08.865
[grunting]

23:16.569 --> 23:18.919
Get down, get down.
Get down, get down!

23:27.014 --> 23:28.842
OK, move, move.

23:28.885 --> 23:30.147
Shh.

23:31.758 --> 23:33.063
Shh.

23:34.021 --> 23:35.414
[branch cracks]

23:35.457 --> 23:36.502
[groaning]

23:36.545 --> 23:38.373
- Jesus.
- Are you OK?

23:38.417 --> 23:40.288
- My ankle.
- Are you OK?

23:40.331 --> 23:41.332
No.

23:41.376 --> 23:42.856
Come on, get up.

23:42.899 --> 23:44.161
Can you walk?

23:45.467 --> 23:47.208
Ah!

23:47.251 --> 23:48.905
I can't.

23:48.949 --> 23:50.254
Ah!

23:50.298 --> 23:51.517
You guys go on without me.

23:51.560 --> 23:54.389
No, we can't just
leave you here.

23:54.433 --> 23:55.869
It's OK.

23:55.912 --> 23:57.523
I'll--I'll keep out of
sight till you're back.

23:57.566 --> 23:59.438
Hey, hey, hey.

23:59.481 --> 24:02.179
Scott, do not get caught.

24:02.223 --> 24:04.181
Understand?
- Yeah.

24:04.225 --> 24:05.444
Thanks for that.

24:08.316 --> 24:09.883
I'll be fine.
- Yeah?

24:09.926 --> 24:11.058
Yeah.

24:24.463 --> 24:25.986
12 steps left.

24:26.029 --> 24:27.291
17 steps right.

24:27.335 --> 24:28.771
13 steps straight.

24:29.642 --> 24:32.166
[grunting]

24:32.209 --> 24:35.038
I know you didn't plan
that escape by yourself.

24:35.082 --> 24:36.562
It was only me.
It was only me!

24:36.605 --> 24:39.478
You're either
brave or stupid!

24:39.521 --> 24:41.088
[speaking native language]

24:44.091 --> 24:45.048
Wait, wait, wait.

24:45.092 --> 24:46.615
You--you're Tongva.

24:48.138 --> 24:52.099
People in the village
that I grew up in,

24:52.142 --> 24:53.535
they spoke your language.

24:57.583 --> 24:59.236
What's your name?

25:02.849 --> 25:06.592
My name is Taamet, but
that's none of your concern.

25:06.635 --> 25:08.289
Wait, Taamet.
Taamet, hey.

25:08.332 --> 25:09.769
Hey, Taamet.

25:09.812 --> 25:13.773
Taamet, the Tongva that
I knew, they were kind.

25:13.816 --> 25:15.296
They were peaceful.
They were compassionate.

25:15.339 --> 25:16.819
They were good people.

25:16.863 --> 25:19.213
What's someone
like you, a Tongva,

25:19.256 --> 25:21.041
doing here with the Exiles?

25:25.654 --> 25:27.743
You think I'm gonna
tell you my story,

25:27.787 --> 25:30.398
and then we'll become friends,
and I'll let you go?

25:30.441 --> 25:32.531
You think I'm stupid like you?

25:32.574 --> 25:34.184
No, no. No, no, no.
Of course not.

25:34.228 --> 25:37.013
But I have a family

25:37.057 --> 25:40.756
that I have to get back to,
that need me.

25:42.802 --> 25:45.065
And I know that's something
that you understand.

25:48.111 --> 25:53.595
I promise you,
you will die here.

25:53.639 --> 25:56.729
And you will never
see your family again.

25:59.209 --> 26:00.515
Taamet.

26:00.559 --> 26:02.343
Teach him a lesson.

26:02.386 --> 26:03.562
Taamet!

26:04.388 --> 26:05.302
Please, don't!

26:06.869 --> 26:09.306
Come on, come on.
It's just up there.

26:09.350 --> 26:10.569
Come on.

26:11.831 --> 26:13.572
Why are we stopping?

26:13.615 --> 26:15.182
Let's just go.
They're gonna see us.

26:15.225 --> 26:16.357
Hey.

26:16.400 --> 26:17.663
Lucas?

26:18.577 --> 26:20.622
Come on!

26:20.666 --> 26:22.972
Ahh!
[gunshot]

26:23.016 --> 26:25.105
- That's him.
- Who?

26:25.148 --> 26:26.889
[grunting]

26:26.933 --> 26:28.064
Ah!

26:29.109 --> 26:30.632
That's the guy
who killed my mom.

26:30.676 --> 26:34.375
<i>♪</i>

26:34.418 --> 26:35.942
What are you gonna do?

26:39.423 --> 26:40.729
I'm gonna kill him.

26:45.168 --> 26:47.649
Lucas, let's just
talk about this.

26:47.693 --> 26:49.390
No, there's nothing
to talk about. Get out my way.

26:49.433 --> 26:52.001
No, this isn't
gonna fix anything.

26:52.045 --> 26:53.307
- Veronica.
- Hey.

26:53.350 --> 26:54.656
Veronica, please.

26:54.700 --> 26:56.266
Just get out of my way.
- Look, I know. I know.

26:56.310 --> 26:57.703
I know that you're
grieving Marybeth,

26:57.746 --> 26:59.182
and if I had to guess,
you probably blame yourself

26:59.226 --> 27:01.620
for what happened, right?

27:01.663 --> 27:04.361
But killing this guy
won't change that.

27:04.405 --> 27:06.015
No, you don't know what
you're talking about.

27:06.059 --> 27:07.364
I do. I know!

27:07.408 --> 27:08.801
I know what it's like
to feel guilt.

27:08.844 --> 27:10.193
I know how it eats at you,
and how you'd do anything

27:10.237 --> 27:11.804
to make it go away.

27:11.847 --> 27:14.067
Even if you kill this guy,

27:14.110 --> 27:16.199
that guilt's not gonna leave.

27:16.243 --> 27:17.461
I promise you.

27:18.680 --> 27:21.552
So let's just take
the food and go.

27:21.596 --> 27:23.206
OK?

27:24.904 --> 27:26.340
Lucas, please.

27:27.776 --> 27:30.257
7, 8, 9, 10,

27:30.300 --> 27:32.433
11, 12, 13.

27:36.132 --> 27:38.352
I guess this is it.
[exhales]

27:43.226 --> 27:45.664
OK, Silas, where'd you put it?

27:48.101 --> 27:49.624
Oh, no.

27:50.756 --> 27:52.235
Come on.

27:52.279 --> 27:53.846
[gasps]
- I'm going in now.

27:56.849 --> 27:58.677
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

27:58.720 --> 28:04.291
<i>♪</i>

28:05.945 --> 28:07.860
[clattering]

28:08.687 --> 28:10.471
[sighs]

28:13.126 --> 28:14.823
That's what I'm talking about.

28:17.696 --> 28:18.871
OK.

28:20.089 --> 28:22.613
[thunder rumbles]

28:25.442 --> 28:27.227
This can't be happening.

28:27.270 --> 28:29.011
Gavin's gonna be OK.

28:29.055 --> 28:30.621
He's tough.

28:35.757 --> 28:37.585
[door opening]

28:39.892 --> 28:41.502
- Get in.
- Gavin!

28:42.677 --> 28:44.374
[grunts]

28:45.811 --> 28:48.814
Ah. I--I could really
use some water.

28:48.857 --> 28:49.945
OK.

28:49.989 --> 28:52.774
[coughs]

28:52.818 --> 28:54.645
[banging]
- Hey!

28:56.299 --> 28:58.562
He needs some water

28:58.606 --> 29:01.217
unless you don't want him
back working for you.

29:01.261 --> 29:02.741
Make it quick.

29:08.268 --> 29:10.400
You shouldn't have done that.

29:10.444 --> 29:12.315
Better one of us
than everyone, right?

29:12.359 --> 29:13.752
[exhales]

29:13.795 --> 29:15.754
I didn't wanna
see you get hurt.

29:16.276 --> 29:18.321
[crying]

29:22.021 --> 29:23.109
What was that for?

29:23.152 --> 29:24.763
Nothing.

29:28.854 --> 29:31.508
You just remind me of
this kid I met down here.

29:31.552 --> 29:36.687
He was really, really kind,

29:36.731 --> 29:38.864
and brave.

29:39.560 --> 29:41.257
And he left the
only home he ever knew

29:41.301 --> 29:43.694
because some strange lady

29:43.738 --> 29:46.697
told him he had to
save her family.

29:46.741 --> 29:49.439
Guess he--he knew
he could trust her.

29:49.483 --> 29:51.572
I've basically known
you your whole life.

29:51.615 --> 29:52.878
Yeah.

29:54.575 --> 29:58.884
You remember when we met,
as adults?

29:58.927 --> 29:59.885
Yeah.

29:59.928 --> 30:01.582
What did I say?

30:02.757 --> 30:04.890
You said

30:04.933 --> 30:07.414
it felt like
you had known me forever.

30:10.373 --> 30:11.722
I guess I was right.

30:16.031 --> 30:18.860
No wonder I fell in love
with you on the spot.

30:23.299 --> 30:24.779
[sighs]

30:24.823 --> 30:27.129
I know about Levi,

30:27.173 --> 30:28.957
why he went to Germany.

30:30.698 --> 30:32.787
He told me before he came down.

30:33.440 --> 30:34.876
I don't blame you.

30:34.920 --> 30:36.356
You lost faith in me.

30:36.399 --> 30:38.314
I get that.

30:38.358 --> 30:40.664
I let--I let you
and everyone down.

30:40.708 --> 30:43.319
I'm gonna do what I can
to earn your trust back.

30:43.363 --> 30:44.930
I am.

30:44.973 --> 30:46.801
Whatever it takes.

30:47.889 --> 30:51.588
And then when we get out of
here, and we get Josh back,

30:51.632 --> 30:56.550
I want us to start again,
start over, just--

30:56.593 --> 30:59.466
just be together as a family.

31:01.076 --> 31:02.643
You and me.

31:06.560 --> 31:09.606
Listen up!
I need everyone in tunnel 4.

31:09.650 --> 31:10.912
Get over there now.

31:10.956 --> 31:13.697
- Taamet.
- We hit a big deposit.

31:13.741 --> 31:16.265
We need it mined in time for
the shipment to the tower.

31:16.309 --> 31:17.876
Get all the
prisoners over there.

31:17.919 --> 31:19.051
Do it now.

31:21.444 --> 31:24.491
You, let's go.

31:32.151 --> 31:33.369
Hey.

31:34.762 --> 31:36.068
[grunts]

31:40.159 --> 31:41.334
All the guards
are in tunnel 4.

31:41.377 --> 31:42.509
No one's around.

31:42.552 --> 31:43.902
This is our chance.

31:43.945 --> 31:45.251
Let's use Gavin's map
and get out.

31:45.294 --> 31:46.382
No, he can barely move.

31:46.426 --> 31:48.428
No, no, no, no.

31:48.471 --> 31:49.995
Levi's right.

31:52.606 --> 31:53.999
We have to try.

32:00.222 --> 32:02.137
[grunts]
- Easy.

32:02.181 --> 32:03.486
I'm good, I'm good, I'm good.

32:03.530 --> 32:04.661
- You sure?
- Yeah.

32:04.705 --> 32:06.402
Let's get
the hell out of here.

32:09.492 --> 32:12.800
[chatter]

32:16.717 --> 32:18.327
You're still awake?

32:18.371 --> 32:20.460
- Dad!
- [laughs]

32:20.503 --> 32:22.157
Time for bed, my boy.

32:22.201 --> 32:23.637
Come on.

32:24.681 --> 32:28.555
[indistinct chatter]

32:29.948 --> 32:31.384
There we go.

32:31.427 --> 32:32.907
Good night, sweetheart.

32:39.218 --> 32:41.002
[exhales]

32:47.443 --> 32:49.141
Did you--

32:54.059 --> 32:55.756
No.

32:58.411 --> 32:59.716
What happened?

32:59.760 --> 33:01.588
I just wanna
get out of here.

33:03.242 --> 33:08.464
<i>♪</i>

33:12.207 --> 33:13.992
[grunts]

33:15.210 --> 33:16.690
OK, OK.

33:16.733 --> 33:18.039
Hey, you're
about to pass out.

33:18.083 --> 33:19.780
Sit down.

33:19.823 --> 33:22.478
According to the map, we're
really close to the exit.

33:22.522 --> 33:23.914
Stay with him.

33:23.958 --> 33:25.133
I'll find out how
much further we are.

33:25.177 --> 33:26.656
Yeah, go.

33:36.753 --> 33:38.364
It's nothing compared
to Kandahar, right?

33:38.407 --> 33:41.671
Hard to top flying a Herc out
of a canyon being chased

33:41.715 --> 33:43.630
by Taliban on horses.

33:43.673 --> 33:45.414
We made it out of that.

33:45.458 --> 33:47.677
We'll make it out
of this mess, too.

33:47.721 --> 33:49.723
We had each
other's backs then.

33:51.551 --> 33:52.987
We still do.

33:55.511 --> 33:57.470
You sure about that?

33:59.167 --> 34:00.560
Over here!
Come on.

34:02.431 --> 34:04.042
Come on, let's go.

34:07.784 --> 34:09.090
Hey, we're close.

34:09.134 --> 34:10.309
It's this way.

34:10.352 --> 34:11.397
Let's go.

34:11.440 --> 34:13.094
Come down here!

34:13.138 --> 34:14.226
Don't move!

34:14.269 --> 34:15.444
Hey.

34:15.488 --> 34:18.230
<i>♪</i>

34:23.104 --> 34:25.280
Your friends should
have left without you.

34:25.324 --> 34:27.935
Maybe they would have made it.

34:27.978 --> 34:30.677
Get out of the way. Now.

34:30.720 --> 34:33.288
[shouting outside]

34:34.855 --> 34:37.162
[both grunting]

34:44.604 --> 34:48.086
If you were smart,
you would kill me now.

34:49.435 --> 34:50.479
[grunts]

34:51.959 --> 34:52.960
- Let's go.
- Come on.

34:53.003 --> 34:54.701
Let's go!

35:02.970 --> 35:04.450
Whoever said
crime doesn't pay

35:04.493 --> 35:06.321
had no idea what they
were talking about.

35:08.280 --> 35:10.630
Well, good job, my friends.

35:10.673 --> 35:12.327
I'll see you later.

35:12.371 --> 35:13.502
Hey.
[whistles]

35:15.200 --> 35:16.810
Where are you going?

35:16.853 --> 35:18.681
Just for a little walk.

35:18.725 --> 35:20.466
What about your ankle?

35:20.509 --> 35:23.033
I find that
moving around helps.

35:24.905 --> 35:26.254
Looks like you
guys were busy.

35:26.298 --> 35:27.821
What the hell did you do?

35:27.864 --> 35:28.952
We took a vote.

35:28.996 --> 35:30.258
Yes, we did.

35:30.302 --> 35:32.130
This is serious, Lucas.

35:32.173 --> 35:33.653
If the village finds
out what you did--

35:33.696 --> 35:35.176
No one saw us.

35:36.177 --> 35:37.657
You're part of this, too?

35:37.700 --> 35:39.224
Oh my God, Ty.

35:39.267 --> 35:42.140
We were all hungry,
so we did what we had to do.

35:42.183 --> 35:43.706
There's gonna
be a price to pay.

35:43.750 --> 35:45.752
Yeah, well, that sounds
like a tomorrow problem to me.

35:45.795 --> 35:48.146
Today, we get to eat.

35:49.538 --> 35:51.061
Have at it.

36:01.333 --> 36:02.856
[branches cracking]
- Whoa.

36:02.899 --> 36:04.031
Scott.

36:04.074 --> 36:05.946
Oh, thank God.

36:05.989 --> 36:07.643
I thought I was going the right
way, but all of these trees

36:07.687 --> 36:09.863
look the same.

36:09.906 --> 36:11.734
Do you have what I asked for?

36:14.084 --> 36:16.478
Listen, I just wanted to
thank you for coming today.

36:19.655 --> 36:21.831
If you weren't there, I don't
know what I would have done.

36:26.314 --> 36:28.098
Can I ask you something?

36:29.578 --> 36:31.667
You wanna know
why I let that guy go.

36:33.016 --> 36:34.757
Yeah.

36:38.239 --> 36:39.632
I wanted to kill him.

36:41.938 --> 36:43.375
I still do.

36:48.206 --> 36:52.210
He was with his family--

36:52.253 --> 36:55.561
his wife,

36:55.604 --> 36:56.866
and a little kid.

37:00.827 --> 37:03.612
Couldn't stop thinking
about my dad,

37:03.656 --> 37:05.527
how he died.

37:15.972 --> 37:18.366
I can't do that to another kid.

37:25.155 --> 37:26.679
Your mom would be proud.

37:27.854 --> 37:29.421
Yeah.

37:29.464 --> 37:30.813
I don't know about that.

37:46.438 --> 37:48.309
You know, I'm not happy.

37:48.353 --> 37:52.487
I had to lie to my
friends, fake an injury,

37:52.531 --> 37:54.663
sneak into Silas's hut,

37:54.707 --> 37:58.450
and commit a 10,000 BC
food heist to get this.

37:59.886 --> 38:01.279
But here it is.

38:03.759 --> 38:04.934
You did well.

38:04.978 --> 38:06.327
Thanks.

38:06.371 --> 38:08.155
Though I gotta admit,
keeping secrets

38:08.198 --> 38:09.809
isn't exactly my forte.

38:09.852 --> 38:12.072
Well, I'm afraid you're
gonna have to keep this one

38:12.115 --> 38:14.117
a little while longer.

38:14.161 --> 38:15.989
No, no, no.

38:16.032 --> 38:18.339
Aldridge, I'm tired
of lying to my friends.

38:18.383 --> 38:22.604
I am trying to protect
your friends, Scott.

38:22.648 --> 38:25.564
This is the only way
I can keep them safe.

38:25.607 --> 38:28.175
Listen, everything is
moving into its right place.

38:28.218 --> 38:30.308
I just need you to be patient.

38:32.701 --> 38:34.181
So what now?

38:34.224 --> 38:36.488
Our first attempt at getting
into the building failed.

38:36.531 --> 38:38.925
But there is another way,

38:38.968 --> 38:42.232
and this will help
get us where we need to go.

38:42.276 --> 38:44.278
[scoffs]

38:44.322 --> 38:46.498
And what do we do
when we get there?

38:46.541 --> 38:48.369
Several things
need to be accomplished,

38:48.413 --> 38:51.372
one of which

38:51.416 --> 38:54.419
is getting your friends
Josh and Riley back.

38:55.942 --> 38:58.379
Wait a second.

38:58.423 --> 39:00.903
You've known how to get
them back the entire time,

39:00.947 --> 39:02.427
and you didn't tell me?

39:02.470 --> 39:04.820
I tell you what
you need to know, Scott.

39:05.430 --> 39:06.996
Unbelievable!

39:12.001 --> 39:16.266
What you need to do now is go
back to the clearing and wait.

39:19.095 --> 39:21.141
What am I waiting for?

39:21.184 --> 39:23.056
For Gavin.

39:23.099 --> 39:27.539
<i>♪</i>

39:27.582 --> 39:28.931
You all right?
Wanna rest?

39:28.975 --> 39:30.585
No, no, no. I--

39:30.629 --> 39:34.197
Everything hurts, but, uh,
it could have been worse.

39:34.241 --> 39:35.764
Something you
guys should know.

39:35.808 --> 39:37.287
I overheard
the guards talking,

39:37.331 --> 39:39.377
said they were taking a
shipment of rock to the tower.

39:41.379 --> 39:43.293
Tower?
You think that's the building

39:43.337 --> 39:44.425
that Silas was talking about?

39:44.469 --> 39:45.992
Whoever is in
the building must be

39:46.035 --> 39:47.472
using it as a fuel source.

39:49.604 --> 39:51.737
Well, what are the
Exiles getting out of it?

39:51.780 --> 39:53.434
Good question.

39:53.478 --> 39:55.784
And we need to be prepared in
case they come looking for us.

39:55.828 --> 39:57.612
- Yeah.
- And what about Virgil

39:57.656 --> 39:58.918
and the others?
We need to help them.

39:58.961 --> 40:00.572
They're still stuck
in that place.

40:00.615 --> 40:02.356
We can make a plan
as soon as we get back.

40:02.400 --> 40:03.966
We're almost there.

40:04.010 --> 40:05.315
- Eve?
- Yeah?

40:05.359 --> 40:07.927
Hey, before you get there,
there's--

40:07.970 --> 40:10.364
look, there's something
I need to tell you.

40:10.408 --> 40:12.540
What?

40:12.584 --> 40:14.542
It's about Izzy.

40:14.586 --> 40:15.587
You said Izzy was fine.

40:15.630 --> 40:17.458
Izzy is fine.
She is.

40:20.722 --> 40:22.463
What?

40:22.507 --> 40:24.509
You're gonna
see for yourself.

40:24.552 --> 40:26.772
What do you mean?

40:26.815 --> 40:28.077
She's here.

40:28.991 --> 40:30.166
She came with me

40:30.210 --> 40:36.956
<i>♪</i>

40:41.090 --> 40:44.224
Izzy!
Izzy!

40:44.267 --> 40:46.182
Mom? Mom?

40:46.226 --> 40:52.667
<i>♪</i>

40:52.711 --> 40:53.929
Izzy.

40:59.718 --> 41:01.981
I decided I was never
gonna see you again.

41:02.590 --> 41:09.118
<i>♪</i>

41:09.162 --> 41:11.033
[laughs]
- I love you.

41:11.077 --> 41:12.818
I love you.

41:24.177 --> 41:25.787
You're OK.

41:28.224 --> 41:35.144
<i>♪</i>
